Title: The Young Pioneers VHS

reviewText: WHAT A WONDERFUL,  WONDERFUL FILM.....This is for the whole family to enjoy. Its the 1870s, and a young couple have just got married.  Wanting to begin their new life out in the wide open plains of Dakota. They settle in a little shack, and fix it up the way they both would like it.  This young couple are very much in love, and that shines throughout this whole film. Looking forward to their happy future togeather, they work hard on the land. Planting Corn and Potatoes, ect. But it also comes with some unexpected set-backs, when they have to battle Snowstorms, Plagues of Grasshoppers, and other Forces ot Nature. But this young couple prove to be strong, and come through it all, with a little help from their distance neighbours. This is the remarkable story of Americas first young Pioneers. It tells of their Tragedys, and of their many Triumphs.
Title: The Young Pioneers VHS

reviewText: Young Pioneers is a fine story of two young people who head to the Dakotas to homestead in the 1870's. A fine story of their lives, one you can watch with anybody. Followed by the sequel Young Pioneers' Christmas.
Title: The Young Pioneers VHS

reviewText: This is the nicest western show I ever saw. Good plot, well chosen actors and actresses, in a convincing and beautiful tale of pioneer life. I could watch it over and over.
Title: The Young Pioneers VHS

reviewText: A likeable, young, couple heads West in a wagon to start a farm on the Great Plains of the Dakota Territory. Very realistic and accurate.The couple face hardships and disasters, but make friends, and press on.Thoughtful and charming.The sequel film, "Young Pioneers Christmas" is just as good, continues the story, and is even more heart-warming.I bought the VHS and copied them to DVD. It was worth the effort, because you come away feeling good.The studios should put these two, excellent, films on DVD today!!
Title: The Young Pioneers VHS

reviewText: I love this movie. I received it promptly in good condition. I would encourage anyone that likes clean movies set back in pioneer times to get this movie.
